article.headline: Kennesaw St. 66, Lipscomb 55
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. (AP) -- Ronell Wooten scored 18 points and Kennesaw State rallied in the second half for a 66-55 win over Lipscomb on Tuesday night. Kennesaw State (5-10 overall, 1-2 Atlantic Sun Conference) trailed 30-27 at halftime and fell behind 40-32 when Trey Williams hit a 3-pointer for Lipscomb (8-6, 1-2) with 17:12 left to play. The Owls then went on an 15-2 run. They took the lead for good at 43-42 on a layup by Golden Ingle with 13:25 to play and finished with Andre Morgan's pair of free throws, which gave Kennesaw State a 47-42 lead with 10:14 left. Ingle's jumper with 5:58 to play gave the Owls a 55-48 lead. Michael Lusk then hit a 3-pointer for the Bisons and Williams followed with a jumper to close the gap to 55-53 with 4:13 left, but that was as close as Lipscomb could get. After Williams missed a 3-point attempt, Brent Ragsdale made a pair of free throws for Kennesaw State for a four-point margin and the Owls pulled away in the final minutes. Eddie Ard scored 25 points to lead the Bisons. Morgan had 14 for the Owls.
